What is Selenium
		- Functional User Interface automation tool / library / framework
		- open source
		- primarily used for web automation - automating your web applications

		- Selenium can only automate browsers

		- Selenium can interact with multiple browsers and different browser versions - 
				Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge, IE, Opera

		- Se supports different programming languages - Java, Python, JS, Ruby, C#, C++
		- Se do not talk to databse directly (you can use JDBC)

To check your drivers in the local system - .cache
To check the dependencies internally in your system - .m2

**************************************************************************************************
DOM - document object model

To open the DOM - Right click --> Inspect
ctrl+shift+I
F12
3 dots on the browser --> More Tools --> Developer Tools

<input class="inputLogin" type="text" id="username" name="USERNAME" size="50">

tagName - purple (input, div, span, label, button) - what type of element it is
attributes - brown (class, id, size, name, type) - before =
attribute values - blue --> after =
text - black --> between the tags

Locators are used to locate the particular web element
Web element - individual element on a web page that can be interacted with using WebDriver

There are 8 type of locators

Locator Preferences

1. id
2. name
3. className




4. linkText

5. tagName
6. partialLinkText
7. XPath
8. CSS selectors


Exception - NoSuchElementException --> whenever you try to access or interact with a web element which
										is not present in the web page


LeafTaps Application

1. Initialize the driver
2. Load the url http://leaftaps.com/opentaps/control/main
3. Maximize the window
4. Enter username
5. Enter password
6. Click Login
7. Get the text of Welcome Demosalesmanager using tagName
8. Click CRM/SFA
9. Get the title of the page
10. Close the window


What is a dropdown according to Se?
	- If the element has the tag <select
	- Select will have multiple <option tags (for every dropdown option)

Steps to handle the dropdown

1. Find WebElement --> Convert to Select class
2. Using Select class --> Choose the dropdown option

Select Methods
1. selectByIndex - index starts at 0 (random data)
2. selectByVisibleText - the text on the option element - one language
3. selectByValue - the attribute (value) on the option - multilingual


WebElement Methods & WebDriver Methods

WebElement Methods
	sendKeys() - type or perform key actions on the input fields
	click() - click a button / input / link / content
	clear() - clears the existing content in the text
	getText() - get the text in the element --> text is present between the tags
	getAttribute() - get the attribute's value in the element


WbDriver Methods
	get() - load the url
	close() - close the browser
	findElement() - locates the element
	getTitle() - Title of the web page
	getCurrentUrl() - URL of the active browser


